Kenya's Onkari Rai on Sunday afternoon finished World Rally Championship (WRC) Safari Rally Kenya 2021 as the highest ranked local.  Kenya’s Karan Patel and Carl "Flash" Tundo came second and third respectively.  Earlier, President Uhuru Kenyatta joined thousands of Kenyans in Naivasha at the Hells Gate WRC Circuit to witness the Power Stage Finish of the 2021 Safari Rally. The Head of State will also preside over the presentation of prizes to the winners of the 2021 WRC Safari Rally at the Kenya Wildlife Service Training Institute (KWSTI).   Battle is now down to Toyota, Hyundai  Suspension problems hit top drivers hard as they race for honours  Onkar Rai: They asked for Safari and they got Safari  Belgian driver Neuville survives punishing opening day to lead Safari Rally  Safari Rally: Driver retires at Stage Seven in Naivasha  By Moses Nyamori and Pkemoi Ngenoh | 3 hours By Stevens Muendo | 2 hours By Hudson Gumbihi | 3 hours ago By Reuters | 3 hours ago